%% Diagram: Cell write path
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant W as Worker (stateless HTTP)
    participant S as Secondary master (random shard)
    participant P as Primary master (shard N)
    participant R as Primary minions (DC2, DC3)

    C->>W: PUT cell (row_key, column, ref_key, body)
    W->>W: hash(row_key) % 4096 -> shard N
    W->>S: insert into buffer table
    S-->>W: ack
    W->>P: insert into entity table (added_id auto-increments)
    P-->>W: ack
    W-->>C: 200 OK (only after BOTH succeed)
    P-)R: async MySQL replication
    Note over S,R: A background reaper polls a primary minion. Once the cell appears it deletes the buffer row on S.
